 My New Year&rsquo;s resolution for 2020 is to break the chains that have been cast upon us by tech companies. This means switching from closed, proprietary software to free and open-source software (FOSS) when possible. It also means being more mindful of who has my personal data, as well as being in as much control over my information as I can be.
